a structured event format for Magic: The Gathering players, focusing on the popular Commander format, allowing players to engage in competitive and casual play while improving their deck-building skills.


Format: Commander 1v1

Style: Round Robin for 7 weeks, 1 match per week. Cut to top 8.

Deck Type: Preconstructed Commander Decklists. Players upgrade their deck each week with $20 worth of TCG Market price.

Games will not be timed. Players life totals start at 40.

https://worldseriesofcommander.com/wsoc-rules/

https://worldseriesofcommander.com/commander-league/


who is this for?
new players or ones returning to magic
show owners that have lots of precons 
opportunity to sell precon ans sleeve bundle
single sales or trades 

at the end players become more familiar with their decks and how to upgrade

week 1 precon unmodified 
following weeks plays add up to $20 upgrades
prices based on cheapest printing available for desieed card(s)
